From 4bfeb54957819f04ff82605e7e31a4f049b590cf Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: vllm-shim <vllm-shim@local>
Date: Thu, 1 Jan 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 1/3] compressed-tensors-mori-epmoe-target

vllm-shim local patch: register MoriEPMoE in compressed-tensors'
target_scheme_map so MoRI-EP MoE layers resolve to the same quant
scheme as their FusedMoE parent.

`CompressedTensorsConfig._add_fused_moe_to_target_scheme_map` aliases
the configured "Linear" scheme onto FusedMoE and DeepEPMoE so that
compressed-tensors checkpoints whose targets list contains only
"Linear" still match the fused-MoE class names returned by
`module.__class__.__name__` in `find_matched_target`. It does not add
MoriEPMoE, which is a sibling subclass of DeepEPMoE under the same
EPMoE -> FusedMoE chain. The result on the SGLang side: when MoRI EP
is selected via `--moe-a2a-backend=mori`, every compressed-tensors
quantized MoE checkpoint (Kimi K2.5/K2.6 INT4, etc.) fails at model
init with:

    ValueError: Unable to find matching target for
    model.layers.N.mlp.experts.0.gate_proj in the
    compressed-tensors config.

The class-name match falls through because "MoriEPMoE" is not a
substring of "Linear", "FusedMoE", or "DeepEPMoE", and the layer-name
match falls through because the config's targets are class names not
regex.

We only add MoriEPMoE here, not NpuFuseEPMoE (NPU-only, not exercised
on the platforms this image targets) or the bare EPMoE base class
(never instantiated directly: get_moe_impl_class always picks a leaf
subclass). Keeping the patch tight reduces the surface area we have
to re-verify on every SGLang bump.

There is no upstream PR for this; the shim carries it locally.
---
 .../layers/quantization/compressed_tensors/compressed_tensors.py | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/python/sglang/srt/layers/quantization/compressed_tensors/compressed_tensors.py b/python/sglang/srt/layers/quantization/compressed_tensors/compressed_tensors.py
index f276fca..af0da5d 100644
--- a/python/sglang/srt/layers/quantization/compressed_tensors/compressed_tensors.py
+++ b/python/sglang/srt/layers/quantization/compressed_tensors/compressed_tensors.py
@@ -202,6 +202,7 @@ class CompressedTensorsConfig(QuantizationConfig):
             return
         self.target_scheme_map["FusedMoE"] = self.target_scheme_map["Linear"]
         self.target_scheme_map["DeepEPMoE"] = self.target_scheme_map["Linear"]
+        self.target_scheme_map["MoriEPMoE"] = self.target_scheme_map["Linear"]
 
     @property
     def weight_block_size(self) -> Optional[List[int]]:
